====Etymology====
:Greek ''megas'', big

#In the [[International System of Units]] and other [[metric]] systems of units, multiplying the [[unit]] to which it is attached by one [[million]].  Symbol: M
#(''Computing'') Multiplying the unit to which it is attached by 2<sup>20</sup> (= 1,048,576).  '''Note: Because this meaning is in conflict with the meaning used with other units, the alternative [[mebi]]- has been proposed.'''
#(''also'' '''[[megalo]]-''' ''or, before a vowel,'' '''megal-''') Very large.
#(''informal'') Very large or impressive.  (''Also written separately as an adjective; see ''Adjective'' below.'')

